* {{a|GA}} {{IPA|en|/ɛ.ksɛ.ksɛks/}}
===Etymology 1===
Very doubtful, although possibly from {{m|en|X}}, a graphic derivative of the {{m|en|skull and crossbones||indicator of death}}; was probably taken from the movie rating of X, which was the rating of movies with mild sexual content in the 1960s and 1970s. The original X certificate was issued from 1951 by the British Board of Film Censors.
